use_geoip.tooltip: Enables or disables geolocation by IP address to set primary/secondary addresses and ports.

show_missed_calls.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to record missed calls for this line.

srtp.tooltip: Enables or disables attempts to encrypt the voice (RTP) of initiated phone calls.  Requires the PBX to also be configured with this option.

rport.tooltip: Request that the server send the response back to the source IP address and port from which the request originated rather than those in the topmost Via header.

udp_keep_alive.tooltip: Enables or disables keep-alive packets sent by the phone through the NAT device to keep the communication port open.

udp_keep_alive_interval.tooltip: The frequency (in seconds) to set a keep-alive packet.

hour_24.tooltip: This setting determines how the time displays on the phone's screen. Select 12:00 a.m. / p.m. to display the time in 12-hour clock notation (for example, 1:00 p.m.). Select 24 to display the time in 24-hour clock notation (for example, 13:00).

timezone.tooltip: Choose the time zone where the phone is located.

dhcp_time.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to update time with the offset time obtained from the DHCP server.

primary_server.tooltip: Choose the primary SNTP server that the phone obtains the time from.

secondary_server.tooltip: Choose the secondary SNTP server that the phone obtains the time from.

format.tooltip: This setting determines how the date displays on the phone's screen. You can display the day, month, and year in a variety of formats.

http.tooltip: Enables or disables the user to access web user interface of the IP phone using the HTTP protocol.

https.tooltip: Enables or disables the user to access web user interface of the IP phone using the HTTPS protocol.

reset_password_required.tooltip: Enable or disable the requirement for password when factory resetting a device.

provisioner.tooltip: Replaces default Provisioning URL with a custom one for white labeling.

firmware.tooltip: Replaces default Firmware URL with a custom one.

area_code.tooltip: When the entered numbers match the predefined area code rule, the IP phone will automatically add the area code before the numbers when dialing out them.

enable.tooltip: This setting enables or disables digitmaps. When enabled, the old style dialplans will no longer work

string.tooltip: All digits that are entered on the phone will be compared with the digitmap specified. If the digits match a digitmap pattern, the call will be automatically placed, without the Send key being pressed.

timeout.tooltip: This setting controls how long, in seconds, each pattern in the digitmap is applied.

number.tooltip: Hotline number that the phone automatically dials out when lifting the handset, pressing the speakerphone key or the line key. Leaving it blank disables hotline feature.

delay.tooltip: The waiting time (in seconds) for the phone to automatically dial out the hotline number.

enabled.tooltip: Prevents user settings from the Web UI from being overwritten during auto-provisioning.

mode.tooltip: Configures the logo mode of the LCD screen.

url.tooltip: Configures the access URL of custom logo file.

custom_config_url.text: Custom Config File URL (V81+ firmware Only)
custom_config_url.tooltip: This setting allows for custom config files to be uploaded which will overwrite settings set via Provisioner

static_ip.tooltip: The IPv4/IPv6 address when the IP address mode is configured 'static'.

static_netmask.tooltip: The IPv4/IPv6 subnet mask when the IP address mode is configured 'static'.

static_gateway.tooltip: The IPv4/IPv6 default gateway when the IP address mode is configured 'static'.

primary_server.tooltip: The primary DNS server used when the IP address mode is configured 'static'.

backup_server.tooltip: The secondary DNS server used when the IP address mode is configured 'static'.

static_dns.tooltip: When enabled the manually configured (static) DNS servers override any provided via DHCP.

ttl_enable.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to use TTL in the A record.

voip_enable.tooltip: It enables or disables VLAN for the Internet (WAN) port.

voip_id.tooltip: The VLAN ID for the Internet (WAN) port when enabled, should be a value between 1 and 4094.

pc_enable.tooltip: It enables or disables VLAN for the PC (LAN) port.

pc_id.tooltip: The VLAN ID for the PC (LAN) port when enabled, should be a value between 1 and 4094.

voip_priority.tooltip: Configures VLAN priority for the Internet(WAN) port.

pc_priority.tooltip: Configures VLAN priority for the PC (LAN) port.

lldp.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to use LLDP.

lldp_interval.tooltip: It configures the interval (in seconds between 1 and 3600.) that how often the phone sends the LLDP request.

cdp.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to use CDP.

cdp_interval.tooltip: It configures the interval (in seconds between 1 and 3600.) that how often the phone sends the LLDP request.

pc_port_mode.tooltip: Configures the way the IP phone processes packets for the PC (LAN) port when VLAN is enabled on the PC (LAN) port.

mtu_value.tooltip: The maximum transmission unit (MTU) of the newtork, should be between 128 and 1500.

pc_port.tooltip: Enables or disables the PC (LAN) port.

min_port.tooltip: The minimum local RTP port, should be a value between 1042 and 65535.

max_port.tooltip: The maximum local RTP port, should be a value between 1042 and 65535.

dscp.tooltip: The QOS DSCP for voice packets (RTP), the default is Expedited Forward (46).

format.tooltip: Configures the call information display method when the phone receives an incoming call, dials an outgoing call or engages in a call.

enabled.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to play a warning tone when it receives a new voice mail.
Enables or disables the phone to play a warning tone when there is a call on hold.

delay.tooltip: The interval (in seconds) at which the phone plays a hold tone when there is a call on hold.

allow.tooltip: Enables or disables the automatical answering of incoming intercom call.

tone.tooltip: Enables or disables the a warning tone when automatically answering an intercom call.

mute.tooltip: Enables or disables the microphone mute when automatically answering an intercom call.

barge.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to automatically answer an incoming intercom call while there is already an active call.

enabled.tooltip: Enables or disables call waiting feature.

tone.tooltip: Enables or disables the phone to play the call waiting tone when the phone receives an incoming call during a call.

internal.tooltip: It configures the desired ring tones for each text.

external.tooltip: It configures the desired ring tones for each text.

handfree.tooltip: Changes the gain for speaker. Range from -50 to 50.

handset.tooltip: Changes the gain for handset. Range from -50 to 50.

headset.tooltip: Changes the gain for headset. Range from -50 to 50.

rule.tooltip: Keys to dial that will send upon pressed.

replace.tooltip: What the prefix is replaced with.
